article.headline: SE Louisiana 51, Texas State 39
article.story: HAMMOND, La. (AP) -- Ricky Woods scored 18 points, leading Southeastern Louisiana to a 51-39 victory over Texas State on Thursday night. Southeastern (13-6, 5-1 Southland Conference) struggled to hit its shots, making only 36.4 percent. But Texas State (9-9, 3-4) connected on only 27.3 percent, including 1-of-13 shooting from 3-point range. Texas State shot 4-of-19 from the field in the first half, falling behind 23-13 at halftime. Southeastern never trailed after Jonathan Patton's 3-pointer put the Lions ahead 5-3. Anthony Dill led Texas State with 15 points. Josh Naylor, who has been the Bobcats' second-leading scorer this season and their top shooter from 3-point range, was held scoreless on 0-for-6 shooting, including 0-for-5 from behind the 3-point arc. Southeastern's Nate Lofton was one of the game's few accurate shooters, going 4-of-5 from the field and making the only free throw he took for nine points.
